  "text": "where m is a bounded measurable function and F κ denotes the Dunkl transform (see the next section). Consider the reflection group G generated by σ j , j = 1, ..., d, the reflection with respect to the hyperplane perpendicular to e j , the j-th coordinate vector, that is to say for every x = (x 1 , ..., x d ) ∈ R d σ j (x) = x − 2 < x, e j > |e j | 2 e j , where e 1 , ..., e d is the standard basis of R d , < ., . > is the usual inner product on R d × R d and |.| is the associated norm. The finite reflection group G is isomorphic to Z where κ 1 , ..., κ d are nonnegative real numbers (let us note that h κ is homogeneous of degree γ κ = d j=1 κ j ). Associated with these objects, the Dunkl differential-difference operators T κ j , j = 1, ..., d, are given by (cf. [CITATION_1] )",
